Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper presents a computational model for analyzing the morphological structure of the lexicon, which falls under the scope of natural language processing and computational linguistics.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The proposed model involves learning and identifying binary relations and analogies between words, which can be seen as a machine learning task.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper presents an AI-based approach for acquiring morphological families and derivational series from a machine readable dictionary.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper does not explicitly deal with computational complexity, but the proposed model may involve some computational challenges that could be relevant to this sub-category.
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries): The paper uses a machine readable dictionary (TLFi) as the dataset for testing the proposed model, which could be relevant to the sub-category of digital libraries.
